 {"id":"bd-wb8f","title":"[EPIC] Async DNS Resolution","description":"# Async DNS Resolution

## Overview
Async DNS resolver with caching, connection reuse, and Happy Eyeballs (RFC 6555) support.

## Why This Is Critical
DNS resolution is required for:
- HTTP client connections
- Any client-initiated network connection
- Service discovery

The standard library's DNS resolution is blocking; we need async resolution for proper integration.

## Core Types

### Resolver
```rust
/// Async DNS resolver.
pub struct Resolver {
    config: ResolverConfig,
    cache: DnsCache,
    // Connection pool for DNS servers
    pool: ConnectionPool,
}

impl Resolver {
    /// Create resolver with system configuration.
    pub async fn from_system_conf() -> Result<Self, DnsError>;

    /// Create resolver with custom configuration.
    pub fn new(config: ResolverConfig) -> Self;

    /// Lookup IP addresses for a hostname.
    pub async fn lookup_ip(&self, host: &str) -> Result<LookupIp, DnsError>;

    /// Lookup with Happy Eyeballs (RFC 6555).
    /// Returns addresses interleaved IPv6/IPv4 for optimal connection racing.
    pub async fn lookup_ip_happy(&self, host: &str) -> Result<HappyEyeballs, DnsError>;

    /// Lookup MX records.
    pub async fn lookup_mx(&self, domain: &str) -> Result<LookupMx, DnsError>;

    /// Lookup TXT records.
    pub async fn lookup_txt(&self, domain: &str) -> Result<LookupTxt, DnsError>;

    /// Lookup SRV records.
    pub async fn lookup_srv(&self, name: &str) -> Result<LookupSrv, DnsError>;

    /// Reverse lookup (PTR record).
    pub async fn reverse_lookup(&self, addr: IpAddr) -> Result<LookupPtr, DnsError>;

    /// Clear the cache.
    pub fn clear_cache(&self);
}
```

### ResolverConfig
```rust
/// DNS resolver configuration.
pub struct ResolverConfig {
    /// DNS server addresses.
    pub servers: Vec<SocketAddr>,
    /// Search domains.
    pub search: Vec<String>,
    /// Number of dots before absolute lookup.
    pub ndots: u8,
    /// Query timeout.
    pub timeout: Duration,
    /// Number of retries.
    pub attempts: u8,
    /// Use TCP for queries.
    pub use_tcp: bool,
    /// Cache configuration.
    pub cache: CacheConfig,
}

pub struct CacheConfig {
    /// Maximum cache entries.
    pub max_entries: usize,
    /// Minimum TTL (floor).
    pub min_ttl: Duration,
    /// Maximum TTL (ceiling).
    pub max_ttl: Duration,
    /// Negative cache TTL.
    pub negative_ttl: Duration,
}

impl ResolverConfig {
    /// Load from /etc/resolv.conf (Unix) or system config (Windows).
    pub fn from_system() -> Result<Self, DnsError>;

    /// Use Google Public DNS.
    pub fn google() -> Self;

    /// Use Cloudflare DNS.
    pub fn cloudflare() -> Self;
}
```

### Lookup Results
```rust
/// IP address lookup result.
pub struct LookupIp {
    query: Name,
    records: Vec<IpAddr>,
    valid_until: Instant,
}

impl LookupIp {
    pub fn iter(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = IpAddr> + '_;
    pub fn is_empty(&self) -> bool;
}

/// Happy Eyeballs iterator.
/// Yields addresses in optimal order for connection racing:
/// IPv6, IPv4, IPv6, IPv4, ...
pub struct HappyEyeballs {
    v6: Vec<Ipv6Addr>,
    v4: Vec<Ipv4Addr>,
    index: usize,
}

impl Iterator for HappyEyeballs {
    type Item = IpAddr;
    // Interleaves v6 and v4 addresses
}

/// MX record lookup result.
pub struct LookupMx {
    records: Vec<MxRecord>,
}

pub struct MxRecord {
    pub preference: u16,
    pub exchange: String,
}

/// SRV record lookup result.
pub struct LookupSrv {
    records: Vec<SrvRecord>,
}

pub struct SrvRecord {
    pub priority: u16,
    pub weight: u16,
    pub port: u16,
    pub target: String,
}
```

### DNS Cache
```rust
/// Thread-safe DNS cache with TTL expiration.
pub struct DnsCache {
    entries: RwLock<HashMap<CacheKey, CacheEntry>>,
    config: CacheConfig,
}

struct CacheKey {
    name: Name,
    record_type: RecordType,
}

struct CacheEntry {
    records: Vec<Record>,
    valid_until: Instant,
    inserted_at: Instant,
}

impl DnsCache {
    pub fn new(config: CacheConfig) -> Self;
    pub fn get(&self, key: &CacheKey) -> Option<Vec<Record>>;
    pub fn insert(&self, key: CacheKey, records: Vec<Record>, ttl: Duration);
    pub fn remove(&self, key: &CacheKey);
    pub fn clear(&self);

    /// Evict expired entries (called periodically).
    pub fn evict_expired(&self);
}
```

## Cancel-Safety
- DNS queries can be cancelled at any point
- Cache updates are atomic
- Connection pool handles cancellation gracefully

## Testing Strategy
- Unit tests with mock DNS server
- Integration tests with real DNS
- Cache TTL and eviction tests
- Happy Eyeballs ordering tests
- Timeout and retry tests
